iven-names>Demétrio</given-names></name><xref ref-type="aff" rid="aff06"/></contrib></contrib-group><aff id="aff01"><institution content-type="orgname">USP</institution><institution content-type="orgdiv1">Escola Politécnica </institution><institution content-type="orgdiv2">Departamento de Engenharia</institution></aff><aff id="aff02"><institution content-type="orgname">USP</institution><institution content-type="orgdiv1">Instituto de Estudos Avançados </institution></aff><aff id="aff03"><institution content-type="orgname">USP</institution><institution content-type="orgdiv1">Instituto de Estudos Avançados </institution></aff><aff id="aff04"><institution content-type="orgname">USP</institution><institution content-type="orgdiv1">Instituto de Estudos Avançados </institution><institution content-type="orgdiv2">Observatório da Inovação e Competitividade</institution></aff><aff id="aff05"><institution content-type="orgname">USP</institution><institution content-type="orgdiv1">Instituto de Estudos Avançados </institution></aff><aff id="aff06"><institution content-type="orgname">Instituto de Pesquisa Econômica Aplicada</institution></aff><pub-date pub-type="epub-ppub"><month>03</month><year>2014</year></pub-date><issue>98</issue><fpage>43</fpage><lpage>67</lpage><permissions><license license-type="open-access" xlink:href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/" xml:lang="en"><license-p>This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License.</license-p></license></permissions><abstract><p>Buscamos ordenar e qualificar uma discussão contemporânea, relativa a uma possível escassez de engenheiros na sociedade brasileira. Com base na literatura, elencamos as hipóteses que levariam à caracterização de escassez e procuramos argumentos baseados em dados para discutir tais hipóteses. Os dados não corroboram a tese de escassez generalizada.</p></abstract><trans-abstract xml:lang="en"><p>In this article, we systematize a contemporary discussion concerning a possible shortage of engineers in Brazilian society. Based on the literature, we list the assumptions that could characterize scarcity and we have looked for data that allow us to test these hypotheses. The data do not support the idea of a general shortage of engineers.</p></trans-abstract><kwd-group xml:lang="pt" kwd-group-type="author-generated"><kwd>Escassez de engenheiros</kwd><kwd>Engenharia</kwd><kwd>Mercado de trabalho</kwd></kwd-group><kwd-group xml:lang="en" kwd-group-type="author-generated"><kwd>Shortage of engineers</kwd><kwd>Engineering</kwd><kwd>Brazilian labor market</kwd></kwd-group><counts><fig-count count="0"/><table-count count="0"/><equation-count count="0"/><ref-count count="18"/><page-count count="25"/></counts></article-meta></front><back><ref-list><ref id="B1"><element-citation publication-type="journal"><article-title>Is there a shortage of scientists and engineers?: How would we know?</article-title><source>Rand Science &amp; Technology Issue Paper</source><date><year>2003</year></date><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Butz</surname><given-names>W.</given-names></name></person-group></element-citation></ref><ref id="B2"><element-citation publication-type="journal"><article-title>Evolução da produtividade total dos fatores na economia brasileira com ênfase no capital humano - 1992-2007"</article-title><source>Revista Brasileira de Economia</source><date><year>2010</year><month>06</month></date><issue>2</issue><volume>64</volume><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>Barbosa Filho</surname><given-names>F. H.</given-names></name><name><surname>Pessôa</surname><given-names>S. A.</given-names></name><name><surname>Veloso</surname><given-names>F. A.</given-names></name></person-group></element-citation></ref><ref id="B3"><element-citation publication-type="journal"><article-title>A demanda por engenheiros e profissionais afins no mercado de trabalho formal"</article-title><source>Radar: tecnologia, p